    <div class="section">
      <h3>HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS</h3>
      <h4>1ST COMPLAINT: SWELLING</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Site: Where did patient first notice</li>
        <ul>
          <li>FROM
            <ol>
              <li>Burn</li>
              <li>Scar</li>
              <li>Pin prick</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li>NAEAVS</li>
        </ul>
        <li>Onset: When did patient notice appearance
          <ul>
            <li>Gradual</li>
            <li>Sudden (after trauma)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Duration
          <ul>
            <li>&Acirc;&plusmn; Painlessness
              <ol>
                <li>Short = Inflammatory [Pain]</li>
                <li>A bit long = Malignant [No pain]</li>
                <li>Long = Chronic inflammation [Less pain]</li>
                <li>Long = Benign [No pain]</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Progression
          <ul>
            <li>Progressive
              <ol>
                <li>Very rapid = Inflammatory</li>
                <li>Rapidly = Malignant</li>
                <li>Slowly = Benign</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Regressive (inflammatory)</li>
            <li>Static</li>
            <li>Static &acirc;&dagger;&rsquo; Rapid [Benign
              &acirc;&dagger;&rsquo; Malignant]</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>A/R</li>
        <li>Associated Symptoms: Patient focuses on pain, ask about other
          symptoms
          <ul>
            <li>Pain</li>
            <li>Fever</li>
            <ul>
              <ul>
                <ul>
                  <ul>
                    <li>septic arthritis</li>
                  </ul>
                </ul>
              </ul>
            </ul>
            <li>Difficulty in respiration</li>
            <li>Difficulty in swallowing</li>
            <li>Interfering with movement</li>
            <li>Disfigurement</li>
            <li>Other swellings
              <ul>
                <li>Neurofibromatosis</li>
                <li>Diaphyseal aclasis</li>
                <li>Hodgkin's disease</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Secondary changes</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Softening</li>
              <li>Ulceration</li>
              <li>Fungation</li>
              <li>Inflammation</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Impairment of function
              <ul>
                <li>Osteosarcoma &acirc;&dagger;&rsquo; Incomplete loss of knee
                  movement; </li>
                <li>Cold abscess &acirc;&dagger;&rsquo; Spine movement</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>MOBILITY</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Nature of movement</li>
              <li>Degree</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Recurrence (after excision)
          <ol>
            <li>Benign &acirc;&dagger;&rsquo; Malignant</li>
            <li>Malignant</li>
            <li>Cyst recurs if wall incompletely removed</li>
          </ol>
          <ul>
            <li>Examples:
              <ol>
                <li>Paget's disease - Recurrent fibroid</li>
                <li>Hydrocele if sac not removed completely</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Weight loss
          <ul>
            <li>TB + Swelling</li>
            <li>Cold abscess + TB</li>
            <li>Malignancy</li>
            <li>AIDS</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
